meta {
  name: GET vehicle-information renders (multi-angle)
  type: http
  seq: 28
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v1/vehicle-information/{{vin}}/renders
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v1.22.x foundation (myskoda PR #571 confirmed live 2026-05-02) —
  Skoda multi-angle composite vehicle renders.

  Source: skodaconnect/myskoda PR #571 ("Api endpoint update",
  merged 2026-05-02T21:12:05Z). Endpoint marked verified (✅) in
  upstream docs/api_endpoints.md after the merge.

  Response shape (verified PR #571 example payload, Enyaq 2021):
    {
      "renders": [],
      "compositeRenders": [
        {
          "layers": [
            {
              "url": "https://iprenders.blob.core.windows.net/...png",
              "viewPoint": "EXTERIOR_SIDE",
              "type": "REAL",
              "order": 0
            }
          ],
          "viewType": "UNMODIFIED_EXTERIOR_SIDE"
        },
        ... 5 more entries (EXTERIOR_FRONT, EXTERIOR_REAR,
            INTERIOR_SIDE, INTERIOR_FRONT, INTERIOR_BOOT) ...
      ]
    }

  Six view points observed in fixture: EXTERIOR_{SIDE,FRONT,REAR},
  INTERIOR_{SIDE,FRONT,BOOT}. Older / less documented vehicles may
  return an empty compositeRenders[] — that is normal.

  Use case: foundation for multi-angle Skoda image entities
  (deferred to next MINOR — adding ~6 ImageEntity per VIN bumps
  entity inventory). Cached 24h via get_vehicle_static_info()
  alongside vehicle-information + equipment.

  Implementation: SkodaClient.get_vehicle_renders() in
  cariad/api/skoda.py. Parser in coordinator._enrich populates
  data["composite_render_urls"]: dict[viewpoint_lower, url].
}
